entries.femaleVariant: Can't believe this suit's the one who's gonna help us.
Oh fuck.
Hm... Unbelievable. It looks like...
Impressive, huh?
What is it?
Impressive, isn't it?
What? What is it?
Where am I? What is this place?
Wanna talk about the biochip.
Motel in the middle of nowhere.
Motel. Middle of nowhere.
Any specific middle?
Doesn't matter. You're not leaving here by yourself anyway.
Got a problem. You're gonna help me kick it.
Nope, got no offer.
Nobody sent me. I got a problem, and you're gonna help me.
You misunderstand me. There is no offer.
What do you want?
What a pity I won't be able to examine it fully.
Yeah, real shame, you coulda been his guinea pig, too.
Tell me how to get rid of it.
I'm afraid I have bad news. Your neural network has completely deteriorated. It can no longer function independently of the chip.
The only thing I could do...
Woo-hoo! It's bargaining time!
...is to give you information on a good clinic in Sweden. They'll help you through the terminal stages, minimize the pain.
[Let Hellman examine biochip] OK.
I don't trust you.
OK.
Whoa. We just met. Haven't built up that sorta trust yet.
How did you think this was going to go?
If you want me to help you, I must examine you.
Why are we here?
Wanna talk about your little invention. Biochip you made for Arasaka.
Fine. But let's get one thing straight first.
Yorinobu Arasaka didn't send you?
This means you must have an offer for me.
If your boss will pay more than Kang Tao, I believe we can talk.
Your tech's tryin' to kill me. Pretty sure that's not how it's advertised.
entries.maleVariant: Your tech is tryin' to kill me. Pretty sure that's not how it's advertised.

entries.femaleVariant: If you wish to file a complaint, I'll need more details.
Got Johnny Silverhand's construct stuck in my head. And I don't want it there.
Your tech's tryin' to kill me.
And what does that have to do with the biochip?
Got Silverhand's construct in my head.
Got Silverhand's construct in my head. It's literally driving me crazy, and I know it's only gonna get worse. That is, unless I remove it.
Klepped it off Yorinobu Arasaka. Job for a client, but the client left me out to dry.
And that, none of that's on the billboards I saw. Not even in the fine print.
You gotta remove the biochip from my system.
Silverhand? Construct... ? That's impossible!
Stole it from Yorinobu Arasaka.
Long story.
You have to remove the biochip from my system.
Long story.
If Arasaka finds me, I'm dead. So are you. So we are in no hurry.
It's not that simple.
Look, you made the thing, didn't you? So where's the problem?
If you're telling the truth, you slotted in a new, experimental version of the biochip.
What's happening to me, exactly?
You said the project was in the trial phase...
Wait, you said the project was in the trial phase.
You don't actually know how it'll end.
What exactly is going on in my head?
You tell me. What's it like to have two personalities?
Oh, I do. I just saw the construct devouring your brain.
It's programmed to take over its new environment. At all costs.
And your little meatbrain is helpless against it.
So no matter what, sooner or later the engram wins?
Yes. And from what I've heard about Silverhand, that seems to be exactly his style.
Because it's not like you're hearing voices. You're both yourself and Silverhand, simultaneously.
Not here to talk philosophy.
I see him, I talk to him.
Didn't come here for the philosophy lecture.
I can see him and talk to him.
It's not philosophy. It's neurobiology. And your evidence just confirmed my hypothesis.
You're not "talking," but yes, I understand what you mean.
Have you noticed the construct's influence on your decision-making?
He can't make me do anything.
What do you mean?
When it comes to my decisions, Johnny really is just a voice in my head.
What do you mean?
Maybe he has a different opinion, but he can't make me do anything.
Agreed, one hundred percent. You are one fucking stubborn host.
You will start doing things that were once unthinkable, at least to your old self.
It's not as if one of you wins the debate. The scale simply shifts, slowly but surely.
And you know exactly who he was. A fanatic. A terrorist. A suicide bomber.
Well fuck me, who's trying to mess with your head now?
At least Johnny never made a whore of himself.
Right, enough of this.
At least Johnny never whored himself out like you.
Know what? That's enough. You just playing for time?
Are you defending him? Or is that Johnny speaking now?
Oh, let me guess – he already tried to take over your body? You know, just for a little while?
Because I can't tell – are you trying to convince me you're useless?
I mean, in that case, I can just shoot you in the head and save us both some time.
Yeah, but I didn't let him.
entries.maleVariant: Yeah. But I didn't let him.

entries.femaleVariant: No.
Next time, you might unexpectedly find it to be an excellent idea.
Yeah. And nothing happened.
You know, this is rather like talking to someone hopelessly in love. Nothing gets through.
You're letting him push you out of your own body. And you can't even see it as a problem.
Would you, though? Could be fun...
Johnny...
Kidding. But watch out – suit's getting ready to talk your head off.
Ugh, finally.
I will try to help you – if you come with me to Kang Tao.
That is why I believe it would be better for you to consider clinical isolation at this stage.
You got it with you?
Better than nothing. Long as we find someone fluent in technobabble.
He's got to. Gonk's fucking useless without 'em.
I always knew Yorinobu's plan would fail. I just never imagined it would turn out like this.
Actually, wasn't a bad idea.
And you decided the best place for it was in your own goddamn head?
Construct rebooted me when my own goddamn head took a bullet.
Arasaka's prize tech really is in the very streets of the city.
No.
And I'm interested. Truly.
Where did you get this biochip?
How's that different from the normal one?
I know you can't just pull it out.
How's the prototype version different? It's got a different engram? Something more...
Right, enough of this.
Right, enough of this.
I know you can't just yank it out.
...aware?
...aggressive?
The biochip is what's unique, not Silverhand's engram.
The previous version of the chip was only used to communicate with pre-saved engrams.
And it was rare as fuck and cost a fortune, yeah.
This one's rarer. Meant to install and activate the engram in a new body.
Guess I'm lucky.
When I left Arasaka, the project was still in the trial phase.
Your tech works, congratulations. Now get it out.
Who could afford this version of the biochip?
Huh, imagine my luck, to be so fucking unique, so fucking exceptional.
How do you put a price on immortality? Who could even afford tech like this?
How exactly was it supposed to work?
How exactly was this new version supposed to work?
Yeah, yeah, great, your tech works. Now get it out of me.
I would have to see it first.
Were you planning to have the engram kick people out of their own bodies? Is that shit by design?
During the tests, we assumed that the body would be... neurally indifferent during implantation.
Y'mean dead?
Yes. Which makes what happened to you interesting indeed.
Nobody. This model was meant to remain in-house.
The prototype was Saburo Arasaka's personal commission. He oversaw the entire project himself.
So if it weren't for Yorinobu, nobody would've found out.
And if not for you, the project would not have been a success. This is a true breakthrough.
That mean you'll help me?
Forget about Kang Tao.
"I'll try" doesn't cut it.
Forget Kang Tao. Got any other ideas?
"I'll try" just isn't gonna cut it. Actually, it's almost like you're trying to buy your way in with the Chinese... at my expense.
Do you even realize how much data is in your head?
Well fuck me sideways, what a halfbrained gonk. He just admitted you're right.
Even if I can't help you, the data must be saved.
If you think there's anyone else who can help you, I could give you the blueprints.
Complete project documentation. Kang Tao offered quite the sum for it.
V.
I'm almost done.
Takemura? What the hell is he doing here?
He's got a few questions of his own for you. You play nice, he might even save your ass.
The blueprints.
He's all yours. I'll give you two some space.
I hope we can come to an understanding.
That is certainly in your best interest.
V. I will remember this.
My ripper said...
Huh. I see my reputation's grown into Arasaka legend.
You showed that to some fucking street doctor? Who else knows?!
I needed help.
Or did you think the first thing that came to mind was downing a Kang Tao AV?
What'll you do with him?
What'll you do with him?
I haven't decided yet.
Hey.
Are you serious?
You know me. I can be impulsive.
[Stand] OK, Goro – all yours.
[Sit] Hey.
Agh, this heat. My throat is positively parched.
Mh, V did not give you even a glass of water?
Unacceptable. Inhumane.
That is not me. You will see the difference. I will give you full buckets.
No, uh… No need.
So, what do you propose?
Well, speak. Say something.
Do you wish to know more about your condition?
You are silent.
Hey.
Where am I? What is this place?
Blackwall somehow affected the chip.
Ain't just about Silverhand anymore. Rogue algos from beyond the Blackwall flipped new switches within the Relic…
What? How could that be?
Is it possible someone who connected to the Blackwall and the Relic could've left... a backdoor? For somethin'... malicious to sneak onto the chip?
This I do not know. The Blackwall – it is Terra Incognita to me. I know just that whatever lies behind it must remain there, at all costs.
At this moment, Silverhand remains your greatest problem. Two psyches molding into one... or is it one psyche cleaving in two? Hmm…
